node.text:
I love a breakfast that sets me up for the day. These plant-based ideas using Weetabix and Alpro products are just so easy to make but delicious to eat. Here's how I made them:

1. Berry compote 🍓 - use any mixed red berries (frozen work too), heat them up with some lemon juice, mash them roughly (careful it’s hot!), then add a bit of sweetener (optional) and voila!
2. Yogurt bowl - add some Alpro Absolutely Oat alternative to yoghurt in a bowl and top it with the berry compote and Weetabix original (Weetabix Protein/Oatibix work great too). For extra flavour, add your favourite herb (I like lemon thyme). 🌱
3. Layered breakfast parfait - in a tall glass or jar, add some Alpro Absolutely Oat alternative to yoghurt, then berry compote, some Weetabix, then repeat to create more layers. Top with some berries and enjoy!
4. Smoothie jar - blend some red berries and Alpro Almond No Sugars Drink. Thinly slice some kiwis and stick them to the inside of a big glass or a jar. Pour in the smoothie and top with a Weetabix biscuit for some crunch. 

Easy and delicious! How do you enjoy your breakfast?

Head over to @weetabixofficial to enter their Veganuary challenge competition for the chance to win a year’s supply of Weetabix and Alpro products (T&Cs apply).

If you love a delicious yogurt bowl with granola then you’ll go crazy for these berry yogurt granola breakfast pizzas 🤩!

node.text:
I made this vegan tart from scratch using some fresh(!) goji berries. We are probably all used to the dried berries but the fresh ones are just on another level - juicy, sweet, refreshing summer fruit 🤩. I am so happy that they are now available at London Marks and Spencer’s food stores @marksandspencerfoodpr , supplied by @iojii_UK [ad] 
If you want to give this recipe a try, here’s all you need:
For the crust:
1.5 cups mixed nuts 
0.5 cup shredded coconut 
6-7 Medjool dates
1/2 tsp salt

For the filling:

1.5 cups goji berries
0.5 cup strawberries
0.5 cup raspberries
2 cups full fat coconut milk
1/4 cup maple syrup
1 Tbsp cornstarch (corn flour)
2 tsp agar agar

To make the base, first blend the nuts to crumbs, then add the dates and salt and blend everything. Spread the crush evenly into a tart tin (8”/20cm). Place it in the fridge or freezer while making the filling.
To make the filling, first blend the berries together. Then pour the mix into a pot, add the rest of the ingredients and warm up over medium heat. When the mixture starts thickening, remove from the heat. You can sieve it to remove the berry pulp but this is optional. Finally, pour over the crust and set aside to cool down and set.

Follow @Gojilovers_UK for more recipes.

YAY or NAY? Roasted beet salad 🥗

This beetroot salad combines peppery arugula with earthy sweet beetroot, creamy goat cheese (optional), and crunchy walnuts with a tangy homemade honey mustard dressing! I simply love making it in the summer - so fresh! 🤩

Check out all the details and lots of tips on my blog, here’s the link:
https://www.alphafoodie.com/roasted-beet-salad-with-goat-cheese/ (link in bio)

Do you like beetroot? Would you try this salad? ☺️

YAY or NAY? Watermelon Cucumber Salad 🍉🤩

This watermelon feta salad is the perfect summer salad. It’s fun, fruity, refreshing, and so easy to make. And did I mention it’s perfect for summer? ☀️

Check out the recipe on my blog, here’s the link:
https://www.alphafoodie.com/herby-watermelon-feta-salad-with-cucumber/

Will you give this salad a try?
